# Error Handling

- Handle errors explicitly at every level - never ignore errors
- Use TypeScript Result/Error types for fallible operations - make errors explicit
- Display user-friendly error messages - never show raw error objects to users
- Log errors appropriately - use console.error for debugging, consider error reporting service
- Use error boundaries for component error handling - catch and display component errors
- Handle API errors gracefully - show appropriate messages for different status codes
- Validate user input before submission - provide immediate feedback
- Handle loading states - show loading indicators during async operations
- Handle empty states - provide meaningful messages when data is empty
- Never use console.error in production - use proper error logging service
